<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-246-980  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 246 980.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  May 8 1989 v23 n19 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Norad site plagued by development problems. (North AmericanAerospace Defense Command)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Betts, Mitch.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The upgrade of communication processors at NORAD is plagued byserious development problems, according to a report by the GeneralAccounting Office (GAO).andP;  The automation effort was scheduled tobe completed by Jun 1988, at a cost of $290 million.andP;  The AirForce estimates that the communication system upgrade will not becompleted until FY 1994 and that the cost will increase to $446million.andP;  The Department of Defense blames Ford Aerospace andCommunications Corp, the prime contractor, for the delay.andP;  Ford'smultilevel security software reduced system performance by 20 to50 percent, according to the GAO.andP;  Ford is accused of ignoringfundamental problems with the system upgrade while continuing tospend money.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ford Aerospace and Communications Corp. (contracts).andO;Topic:     North American Aerospace Defense CommandMilitaryAutomationDefense ContractsUnited States. Air Force.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>